<h2 id="active-learning-and-psychological-models-of-uncertainty-and-information-acquisition">Active learning and psychological models of uncertainty and information acquisition</h2>

<p>Another theme of earlier, but still ongoing, work is is trying to understand how humans ask questions and gather information using formal methods from <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bayesian_experimental_design">optimal experimental design and Bayesian statistics</a>. One of the tasks we use to study this is a probabilistic version of the popular code breaking game <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mastermind_(board_game)">Mastermind</a>, where the subject must guess codes that are generated from distributions over a set of items.</p>

